These folders contain the simulations from the first version of the manuscript "Horseshoe Forests for High-Dimensional Causal Survival Analysis", as can be found in version control on arXiv.

Note: The code uses old versions of the software packages and needs to be updated in order to be run.

Each folder contains the code to run the simulation and generate the graphics. It also contains the results of the simulation stored in .rds files.

The following simulations were performed:
- Main simulation. In the folder: 'Main sim'
- Friedman simulation over more p. In the folder: 'Deeper Friedman'
- Simulation with highly correlated covariates. In the folder: 'Robust sim'
- Simulation with a misspecified error distribution. In the folder: 'Robust sim'
- Simulation with a dense model. In the folder: 'Robust sim'

Additionally, 'continuous.R' contains code for a continuous outcome simulation.